Rangers beat Hearts 2-1 in the Scottish Championship on Sunday . 
  Kenny Miller and Haris Vuckic scored the goals for the Ibrox side . 
  Rangers captain Lee McCulloch was sent off for an elbow on Osman Sow . 
  Stuart McCall says McCulloch apologised to him and the players after the game . 
  Rangers are now second in the table and have won three in a row . 
 